# The vendored tiktoken BPE cache file must be treated as binary. Its filename is a sha1 hash
# that tiktoken looks up directly, and its contents are checked against a hardcoded sha256 hash
# at load time (see tiktoken/load.py). Line-ending normalization (LF -> CRLF on Windows checkout)
# would silently corrupt it and break that integrity check.
core/tiktoken_cache/* binary
